4. Rationale

This design introduces three benefits:

1. Human-first DSL

Syntax readable in voice and text contexts.

Example:

walk 2s -> run 5s


⸻

2. Clean CLI Output

Hiding hashes reduces noise for both humans and AI systems.

Most users care about meaningful revisions, not identifiers.

⸻

3. Deterministic Artifact History

Every revision is:
	•	timestamped
	•	immutable
	•	retrievable

This supports:
	•	reproducibility
	•	debugging
	•	civilization-scale knowledge archives

⸻

5. Future Extensions

Potential expansions of the sequence primitive:

parallel
conditional branches
sensor triggers

Example:

walk 3s -> if obstacle -> stop

These remain optional layers built atop the base -> primitive.

⸻

Summary

This addendum introduces:
	1.	Temporal sequence primitive (->)
	2.	Hidden hash identifiers
	3.	Date-indexed artifact history queries

The goal is to keep the Beast DSL:
	•	minimal
	•	human-readable
