Core DSL Philosophy

Beast2 DSL is based on three core ideas:
	1.	Everything important becomes an artifact
	2.	Artifacts evolve through transformations
	3.	Humans remain the captain of execution

⸻

Primitive: Artifact

Artifacts represent stored knowledge.

Examples:

artifact source_code
artifact animation_walk
artifact dataset_raw
artifact experiment_result

Properties:

• immutable
• timestamped
• reproducible
• hash-addressed (hidden by default)

Hashes remain hidden unless explicitly requested.

⸻

Primitive: Transformation

Transformation uses the pipeline operator:

->

Meaning:

Directed change from one artifact or state to another.

Example:

source_code -> compile -> test -> release

Animation example:

walk 2s -> run 5s

Scientific experiment example:

sample -> heat 400C -> measure -> record


⸻

